@judaspriest The v1.79.0 community release is available here: https://github.com/robertpopa22/mRemoteNG/releases/tag/v1.79.0

3 platform builds (x64, x86, ARM64) available for download. This includes the .NET 10 migration and all 26 fixes from the release cycle.

Please retest with this build and let us know if the issue persists.

@Kvarkas You're absolutely right, and I sincerely apologize for the notification flood. The comments were posted in bulk by an automated script and I should have reviewed the approach before running it. That was a misstep on my part.

I genuinely appreciate the work you've been doing on mRemoteNG and I'd love to coordinate rather than work in parallel. If you're open to it, I'd be happy to discuss directly — whether here on GitHub, or any other channel you prefer.

Again, sorry for the noise, and thank you for your patience.
